goals.question: What is the distribution of flight delays?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the frequency of flight delays and the range of delay times.

goals.question: What is the average distance of flights?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify the median distance of flights and the range of distances.

goals.question: What is the distribution of flights by origin airport?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the frequency of flights from each origin airport.

goals.question: What is the distribution of flights by destination airport?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the frequency of flights to each destination airport.

goals.question: What is the relationship between flight delay and distance?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of delay and distance
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify any correlation between flight delay and distance.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True, color='blue', bins=30)
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['delay'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of flight delays?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Delay (minutes)")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.boxplot(data=data, y='distance')
    plt.axhline(data['distance'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['distance'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the average distance of flights?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.countplot(x="origin", data=data, palette="viridis")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of flights by origin airport?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Origin Airport")
    plt.ylabel("Number of Flights")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('destination').size().reset_index(name='count')
    chart = sns.barplot(x='destination', y='count', data=data, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flights by destination airport?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.xlabel('Destination Airport')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Flights')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%m%d%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='distance', y='delay')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between flight delay and distance?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Distance (miles)')
    plt.ylabel('Delay (minutes)')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
